{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":439,"text":"Hi everybody. So my name is Mac."},{"time":2531,"text":"My job is that I lie to children,"},{"time":6589,"text":"but they're honest lies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":8605,"text":"I write children's books,"},{"time":10373,"text":"and there's a quote from Pablo Picasso,"},{"time":13601,"text":"\"We all know that Art is not truth."},{"time":16787,"text":"Art is a lie that makes us realize truth"},{"time":20429,"text":"or at least the truth that is \ngiven us to understand."},{"time":23127,"text":"The artist must know the manner whereby"},{"time":25237,"text":"to convince others of the \ntruthfulness of his lies.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":30074,"text":"I first heard this when I was a kid,"},{"time":32932,"text":"and I loved it,"},{"time":34623,"text":"but I had no idea what it meant."},{"time":37415,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":38992,"text":"So I thought, you know what, it's what I'm here"},{"time":40889,"text":"to talk to you today about, though,"},{"time":42508,"text":"truth and lies, fiction and reality."},{"time":44721,"text":"So how could I untangle"},{"time":46573,"text":"this knotted bunch of sentences?"},{"time":49100,"text":"And I said, I've got PowerPoint.\nLet's do a Venn diagram."},{"time":52527,"text":"[\"Truth. Lies.\"]\n(Laughter)"},{"time":55020,"text":"So there it is, right there, boom."},{"time":56780,"text":"We've got truth and lies"},{"time":58485,"text":"and then there's this little space,"},{"time":59557,"text":"the edge, in the middle."},{"time":61118,"text":"That liminal space, that's art."},{"time":67918,"text":"All right. Venn diagram. (Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":72915,"text":"But that's actually not very helpful either."},{"time":75941,"text":"The thing that made me understand"},{"time":80316,"text":"that quote and really kind of what art,"},{"time":82806,"text":"at least the art of fiction, was,"},{"time":85023,"text":"was working with kids."},{"time":86463,"text":"I used to be a summer camp counselor."},{"time":88723,"text":"I would do it on my summers off from college,"},{"time":91010,"text":"and I loved it."},{"time":94389,"text":"It was a sports summer camp"},{"time":96148,"text":"for four- to six-year-olds."},{"time":97982,"text":"I was in charge of the four-year-olds,"},{"time":99628,"text":"which is good, because"},{"time":101431,"text":"four-year-olds can't play \nsports, and neither can I."},{"time":104780,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":106355,"text":"I play sports at a four-year-old level,"},{"time":109280,"text":"so what would happen is the kids would"},{"time":112997,"text":"dribble around some cones, and then got hot,"},{"time":114696,"text":"and then they would go sit underneath the tree"},{"time":116959,"text":"where I was already sitting — (Laughter) —"},{"time":119804,"text":"and I would just make up stories and tell them to them"},{"time":122349,"text":"and I would tell them stories about my life."},{"time":124168,"text":"I would tell them about how, on the weekends,"},{"time":125911,"text":"I would go home and I would\nspy for the Queen of England."},{"time":129126,"text":"And soon, other kids"},{"time":132447,"text":"who weren't even in my group of kids,"},{"time":134287,"text":"they would come up to me, and they would say,"},{"time":135756,"text":"\"You're Mac Barnett, right?"},{"time":137668,"text":"You're the guy who spies for the Queen of England.\""},{"time":140737,"text":"And I had been waiting my whole life for strangers"},{"time":143959,"text":"to come up and ask me that question."},{"time":146389,"text":"In my fantasy, they were svelte Russian women,"},{"time":148662,"text":"but, you know, four-year-olds —"},{"time":149899,"text":"you take what you can get in Berkeley, California."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154528,"text":"And I realized that the stories that I was telling"},{"time":158956,"text":"were real in this way that was familiar to me"},{"time":162453,"text":"and really exciting."},{"time":163658,"text":"I think the pinnacle of this for \nme — I'll never forget this —"},{"time":165864,"text":"there was this little girl \nnamed Riley. She was tiny,"},{"time":168687,"text":"and she used to always take \nout her lunch every day"},{"time":171126,"text":"and she would throw out her fruit."},{"time":173466,"text":"She would just take her fruit,"},{"time":174874,"text":"her mom packed her a melon every day,"},{"time":176222,"text":"and she would just throw it in the ivy"},{"time":177971,"text":"and then she would eat fruit snacks"},{"time":180284,"text":"and pudding cups, and I was like, \"Riley,"},{"time":182657,"text":"you can't do that, you \nhave to eat the fruit.\""},{"time":185713,"text":"And she was like, \"Why?\""},{"time":187530,"text":"And I was like, \"Well, when\nyou throw the fruit in the ivy,"},{"time":189362,"text":"pretty soon, it's going to be overgrown with melons,\""},{"time":193254,"text":"which is why I think I ended up"},{"time":195256,"text":"telling stories to children and not\nbeing a nutritionist for children."},{"time":200875,"text":"And so Riley was like, \"That will never happen."},{"time":202763,"text":"That's not going to happen.\""},{"time":203863,"text":"And so, on the last day of camp,"},{"time":206914,"text":"I got up early and I got a big cantaloupe"},{"time":209367,"text":"from the grocery store"},{"time":211393,"text":"and I hid it in the ivy,"},{"time":213495,"text":"and then at lunchtime, I was like,"},{"time":214946,"text":"\"Riley, why don't you go over\nthere and see what you've done.\""},{"time":217621,"text":"And — (Laughter) —"},{"time":220796,"text":"she went trudging through \nthe ivy, and then her eyes"},{"time":223474,"text":"just got so wide, and she pointed out this melon"},{"time":225566,"text":"that was bigger than her head,"},{"time":227680,"text":"and then all the kids ran over \nthere and rushed around her,"},{"time":230650,"text":"and one of the kids was like, \"Hey,"},{"time":232237,"text":"why is there a sticker on this?\""},{"time":234126,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":237350,"text":"And I was like, \"That is also why I say"},{"time":239819,"text":"do not throw your stickers in the ivy."},{"time":242811,"text":"Put them in the trash can. It\nruins nature when you do this.\""},{"time":248283,"text":"And Riley carried that melon around with her all day,"},{"time":253633,"text":"and she was so proud."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255661,"text":"And Riley knew she didn't \ngrow a melon in seven days,"},{"time":260505,"text":"but she also knew that she did,"},{"time":263441,"text":"and it's a weird place,"},{"time":265657,"text":"but it's not just a place that kids can get to."},{"time":268402,"text":"It's anything. Art can get us to that place."},{"time":271934,"text":"She was right in that place in the middle,"},{"time":273891,"text":"that place which you could call art or fiction."},{"time":277316,"text":"I'm going to call it wonder."},{"time":279381,"text":"It's what Coleridge called the\nwilling suspension of disbelief"},{"time":282010,"text":"or poetic faith,"},{"time":283690,"text":"for those moments where a\nstory, no matter how strange,"},{"time":286100,"text":"has some semblance of the truth,"},{"time":288140,"text":"and then you're able to believe it."},{"time":290117,"text":"It's not just kids who can get there."},{"time":291747,"text":"Adults can too, and we get there when we read."},{"time":294436,"text":"It's why in two days, people will be"},{"time":296686,"text":"descending on Dublin to take the walking tour"},{"time":300220,"text":"of Bloomsday and see everything\nthat happened in \"Ulysses,\""},{"time":305825,"text":"even though none of that happened."},{"time":308080,"text":"Or people go to London and they visit Baker Street"},{"time":310337,"text":"to see Sherlock Holmes' apartment,"},{"time":311809,"text":"even though 221B is just a number that was painted"},{"time":313936,"text":"on a building that never \nactually had that address."},{"time":317082,"text":"We know these characters aren't real,"},{"time":318807,"text":"but we have real feelings about them,"},{"time":321427,"text":"and we're able to do that."},{"time":322471,"text":"We know these characters aren't real,"},{"time":324364,"text":"and yet we also know that they are."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327682,"text":"Kids can get there a lot more easily than adults can,"},{"time":331338,"text":"and that's why I love writing for kids."},{"time":332891,"text":"I think kids are the best audience"},{"time":334871,"text":"for serious literary fiction."},{"time":339260,"text":"When I was a kid,"},{"time":342084,"text":"I was obsessed with secret door novels,"},{"time":344710,"text":"things like \"Narnia,\""},{"time":345871,"text":"where you would open a wardrobe\nand go through to a magical land."},{"time":349574,"text":"And I was convinced that secret doors really did exist"},{"time":352304,"text":"and I would look for them and try to go through them."},{"time":354332,"text":"I wanted to live and cross over into \nthat fictional world, which is —"},{"time":358076,"text":"I would always just open people's closet doors. \n(Laughter)"},{"time":363771,"text":"I would just go through my mom's boyfriend's closet,"},{"time":366548,"text":"and there was not a secret magical land there."},{"time":368798,"text":"There was some other weird stuff that\nI think my mom should know about."},{"time":371386,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":373107,"text":"And I was happy to tell her all about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379545,"text":"After college, my first job was working"},{"time":383683,"text":"behind one of these secret doors."},{"time":386231,"text":"This is a place called 826 Valencia."},{"time":388188,"text":"It's at 826 Valencia Street"},{"time":390280,"text":"in the Mission in San Francisco,"},{"time":392766,"text":"and when I worked there, there\nwas a publishing company"},{"time":394792,"text":"headquartered there called McSweeney's,"},{"time":397431,"text":"a nonprofit writing center called 826 Valencia,"},{"time":400585,"text":"but then the front of it"},{"time":402790,"text":"was a strange shop."},{"time":404360,"text":"You see, this place was zoned retail,"},{"time":405787,"text":"and in San Francisco, they were\nnot going to give us a variance,"},{"time":408903,"text":"and so the writer who founded\nit, a writer named Dave Eggers,"},{"time":411790,"text":"to come into compliance \nwith code, he said, \"Fine,"},{"time":414129,"text":"I'm just going to build a pirate supply store.\""},{"time":418505,"text":"And that's what he did. (Laughter)"},{"time":421583,"text":"And it's beautiful. It's all wood."},{"time":423534,"text":"There's drawers you can pull out and get citrus"},{"time":425464,"text":"so you don't get scurvy."},{"time":428483,"text":"They have eyepatches in lots of colors,"},{"time":430631,"text":"because when it's springtime, pirates want to go wild."},{"time":433331,"text":"You don't know. Black is boring. Pastel."},{"time":437674,"text":"Or eyes, also in lots of colors,"},{"time":439670,"text":"just glass eyes, depending on how you want"},{"time":441475,"text":"to deal with that situation."},{"time":445187,"text":"And the store, strangely,"},{"time":448312,"text":"people came to them and bought things,"},{"time":452324,"text":"and they ended up paying the rent"},{"time":454151,"text":"for our tutoring center, which was behind it,"},{"time":456215,"text":"but to me, more important was the fact"},{"time":459267,"text":"that I think the quality of work you do,"},{"time":461918,"text":"kids would come and get instruction in writing,"},{"time":464404,"text":"and when you have to walk this weird, liminal,\nfictional space like this to go do your writing,"},{"time":468670,"text":"it's going to affect the kind of work that you make."},{"time":472420,"text":"It's a secret door that you can walk through."}]},{"cues":[{"time":474607,"text":"So I ran the 826 in Los Angeles,"},{"time":477358,"text":"and it was my job to build the store down there."},{"time":480840,"text":"So we have The Echo Park Time Travel Mart."},{"time":484400,"text":"That's our motto: \"Whenever\nyou are, we're already then.\""},{"time":487240,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":491100,"text":"And it's on Sunset Boulevard in Los Angeles."},{"time":495857,"text":"Our friendly staff is ready to help you."},{"time":497967,"text":"They're from all eras,"},{"time":500110,"text":"including just the 1980s, that guy on the end,"},{"time":503719,"text":"he's from the very recent past."},{"time":505916,"text":"There's our Employees of the Month,"},{"time":507618,"text":"including Genghis Khan, Charles Dickens."},{"time":510604,"text":"Some great people have come up through our ranks."},{"time":513596,"text":"This is our kind of pharmacy section."},{"time":515947,"text":"We have some patent medicines,"},{"time":517286,"text":"Canopic jars for your organs,"},{"time":519637,"text":"communist soap that says,"},{"time":521271,"text":"\"This is your soap for the year.\"\n(Laughter)"},{"time":525722,"text":"Our slushy machine broke"},{"time":527938,"text":"on the opening night and \nwe didn't know what to do."},{"time":530571,"text":"Our architect was covered in red syrup."},{"time":532810,"text":"It looked like he had just murdered somebody,"},{"time":535284,"text":"which it was not out of the question"},{"time":536971,"text":"for this particular architect,"},{"time":539021,"text":"and we didn't know what to do."},{"time":540607,"text":"It was going to be the highlight of our store."},{"time":541639,"text":"So we just put that sign on it that said,"},{"time":542984,"text":"\"Out of order. Come back yesterday.\"\n(Laughter)"},{"time":547489,"text":"And that ended up being a better joke than slushies,"},{"time":549525,"text":"so we just left it there forever."},{"time":553621,"text":"Mammoth Chunks. These things\nweigh, like, seven pounds each."},{"time":557934,"text":"Barbarian repellent. It's full of salad"},{"time":560134,"text":"and potpourri — things that barbarians hate."},{"time":564712,"text":"Dead languages."},{"time":566670,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":569370,"text":"Leeches, nature's tiny doctors."},{"time":572450,"text":"And Viking Odorant, which\ncomes in lots of great scents:"},{"time":575590,"text":"toenails, sweat and rotten vegetables, pyre ash."},{"time":579595,"text":"Because we believe that Axe Body Spray"},{"time":581703,"text":"is something that you should\nonly find on the battlefield,"},{"time":583366,"text":"not under your arms.\n(Laughter)"},{"time":587560,"text":"And these are robot emotion chips,"},{"time":589544,"text":"so robots can feel love or fear."},{"time":591771,"text":"Our biggest seller is Schadenfreude,"},{"time":593481,"text":"which we did not expect."},{"time":594782,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":595793,"text":"We did not think that was going to happen."},{"time":598240,"text":"But there's a nonprofit behind it,"},{"time":600501,"text":"and kids go through a door\nthat says \"Employees Only\""},{"time":602481,"text":"and they end up in this space"},{"time":603696,"text":"where they do homework and write stories"},{"time":605870,"text":"and make films and this is a book release party"},{"time":608330,"text":"where kids will read."},{"time":609814,"text":"There's a quarterly that's published"},{"time":611716,"text":"with just writing that's done by the kids"},{"time":613145,"text":"who come every day after school,"},{"time":614202,"text":"and we have release parties"},{"time":615730,"text":"and they eat cake and read for their parents"},{"time":618677,"text":"and drink milk out of champagne glasses."},{"time":621529,"text":"And it's a very special space,"},{"time":624777,"text":"because it's this weird space in the front."},{"time":627996,"text":"The joke isn't a joke."},{"time":631295,"text":"You can't find the seams on the fiction,"},{"time":633695,"text":"and I love that. It's this little bit of fiction"},{"time":636603,"text":"that's colonized the real world."},{"time":639865,"text":"I see it as kind of a book in three dimensions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":643922,"text":"There's a term called metafiction,"},{"time":646162,"text":"and that's just stories about stories,"},{"time":650245,"text":"and meta's having a moment now."},{"time":651820,"text":"Its last big moment was probably in the 1960s"},{"time":653845,"text":"with novelists like John Barth and William Gaddis,"},{"time":656522,"text":"but it's been around."},{"time":657770,"text":"It's almost as old as storytelling itself."},{"time":661311,"text":"And one metafictive technique"},{"time":663851,"text":"is breaking the fourth wall. Right?"},{"time":665645,"text":"It's when an actor will turn to the audience"},{"time":668895,"text":"and say, \"I am an actor,"},{"time":669961,"text":"these are just rafters.\""},{"time":672552,"text":"And even that supposedly honest moment,"},{"time":674577,"text":"I would argue, is in service of the lie,"},{"time":676803,"text":"but it's supposed to foreground the artificiality"},{"time":679559,"text":"of the fiction."},{"time":681246,"text":"For me, I kind of prefer the opposite."},{"time":683395,"text":"If I'm going to break down the fourth wall,"},{"time":685529,"text":"I want fiction to escape"},{"time":687872,"text":"and come into the real world."},{"time":689955,"text":"I want a book to be a secret door that opens"},{"time":694554,"text":"and lets the stories out into reality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":697446,"text":"And so I try to do this in my books."},{"time":700427,"text":"And here's just one example."},{"time":701970,"text":"This is the first book that I ever made."},{"time":703892,"text":"It's called \"Billy Twitters\nand his Blue Whale Problem.\""},{"time":706513,"text":"And it's about a kid who gets a blue whale as a pet"},{"time":708643,"text":"but it's a punishment"},{"time":710229,"text":"and it ruins his life."},{"time":712704,"text":"So it's delivered overnight by FedUp."},{"time":715516,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":718106,"text":"And he has to take it to school with him."},{"time":720100,"text":"He lives in San Francisco —"},{"time":721454,"text":"very tough city to own a blue whale in."},{"time":723985,"text":"A lot of hills, real estate is at a premium."},{"time":728419,"text":"This market's crazy, everybody."},{"time":730927,"text":"But underneath the jacket is this case,"},{"time":734718,"text":"and that's the cover underneath the book, the jacket,"},{"time":738904,"text":"and there's an ad"},{"time":740284,"text":"that offers a free 30-day risk-free trial"},{"time":743527,"text":"for a blue whale."},{"time":745426,"text":"And you can just send in a\nself-addressed stamped envelope"},{"time":748420,"text":"and we'll send you a whale."},{"time":752270,"text":"And kids do write in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756610,"text":"So here's a letter. It says, \"Dear people,"},{"time":760018,"text":"I bet you 10 bucks you won't send me a blue whale."},{"time":763199,"text":"Eliot Gannon (age 6).\""},{"time":765676,"text":"(Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":770838,"text":"So what Eliot and the other kids"},{"time":772960,"text":"who send these in get back"},{"time":775451,"text":"is a letter in very small print\nfrom a Norwegian law firm —"},{"time":778376,"text":"(Laughter) —"},{"time":782337,"text":"that says that due to a change in customs laws,"},{"time":785698,"text":"their whale has been held up in Sognefjord,"},{"time":787905,"text":"which is a very lovely fjord,"},{"time":789129,"text":"and then it just kind of talks about Sognefjord"},{"time":790593,"text":"and Norwegian food for \na little while. It digresses."},{"time":793073,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":796767,"text":"But it finishes off by saying that"},{"time":798680,"text":"your whale would love to hear from you."},{"time":801414,"text":"He's got a phone number,"},{"time":803000,"text":"and you can call and leave him a message."},{"time":807714,"text":"And when you call and leave him a message,"},{"time":810290,"text":"you just, on the outgoing message,"},{"time":812281,"text":"it's just whale sounds and then a beep,"},{"time":817399,"text":"which actually sounds a lot like a whale sound."},{"time":820954,"text":"And they get a picture of their whale too."},{"time":822934,"text":"So this is Randolph,"},{"time":825465,"text":"and Randolph belongs to a kid named Nico"},{"time":828806,"text":"who was one of the first kids to ever call in,"},{"time":833088,"text":"and I'll play you some of Nico's message."},{"time":835398,"text":"This is the first message I ever got from Nico."}]},{"cues":[{"time":839530,"text":"(Audio) Nico: Hello, this is Nico."},{"time":841769,"text":"I am your owner, Randolph. Hello."},{"time":845803,"text":"So this is the first time I can ever talk to you,"},{"time":849279,"text":"and I might talk to you soon another day. Bye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":855523,"text":"Mac Barnett: So Nico called back, like, an hour later."},{"time":858110,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":860360,"text":"And here's another one of Nico's messages."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864297,"text":"(Audio) Nico: Hello, Randolph, this is Nico."},{"time":867840,"text":"I haven't talked to you for a long time,"},{"time":872993,"text":"but I talked to you on Saturday or Sunday,"},{"time":877688,"text":"yeah, Saturday or Sunday,"},{"time":879938,"text":"so now I'm calling you again"},{"time":882953,"text":"to say hello and I wonder what you're doing right now,"},{"time":887869,"text":"and I'm going to probably call you again"},{"time":890805,"text":"tomorrow or today,"},{"time":892988,"text":"so I'll talk to you later. Bye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":897184,"text":"MB: So he did, he called back that day again."},{"time":901492,"text":"He's left over 25 messages for Randolph"},{"time":905373,"text":"over four years."},{"time":908125,"text":"You find out all about him"},{"time":910216,"text":"and the grandma that he loves"},{"time":911852,"text":"and the grandma that \nhe likes a little bit less —"},{"time":914207,"text":"(Laughter) —"},{"time":916400,"text":"and the crossword puzzles that he does,"},{"time":918827,"text":"and this is — I'll play you one \nmore message from Nico."},{"time":922607,"text":"This is the Christmas message from Nico."}]},{"cues":[{"time":925910,"text":"[Beep] (Audio) Nico: Hello, Randolph,"},{"time":928273,"text":"sorry I haven't talked to you in a long time."},{"time":931528,"text":"It's just that I've been so busy"},{"time":934194,"text":"because school started,"},{"time":936893,"text":"as you might not know, probably,"},{"time":939926,"text":"since you're a whale, you don't know,"},{"time":943807,"text":"and I'm calling you to just say,"},{"time":948487,"text":"to wish you a merry Christmas."},{"time":952177,"text":"So have a nice Christmas,"},{"time":956778,"text":"and bye-bye, Randolph. Goodbye."},{"time":963651,"text":"MB: I actually got Nico,"},{"time":965175,"text":"I hadn't heard from in 18 months,"},{"time":968306,"text":"and he just left a message two days ago."},{"time":972424,"text":"His voice is completely different,"},{"time":974850,"text":"but he put his babysitter on the phone,"},{"time":978350,"text":"and she was very nice to Randolph as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":982211,"text":"But Nico's the best reader I could hope for."},{"time":986561,"text":"I would want anyone I was writing for"},{"time":990287,"text":"to be in that place emotionally"},{"time":992428,"text":"with the things that I create."},{"time":994664,"text":"I feel lucky. Kids like Nico are the best readers,"},{"time":998365,"text":"and they deserve the best stories we can give them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1001960,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1004162,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}